---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHeader from '../../components/PageHeader.astro';
import Section from '../../components/Section.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';

/**
 * Introduction — explains what this system is, who uses it, and how it's structured.
 * First page a new team member should read.
 */
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Introduction"
  description="What the Increments Inc. design system is, who it's for, and how to use it."
>
  <PageHeader
    eyebrow="01 · Foundation"
    title="Introduction"
    italicWord="Introduction"
    lede="The system that keeps every Increments Inc. surface — product, marketing, sales, partner collateral — looking like it came from the same company. Start here before touching any design or code."
  />

  <Section title="What this is">
    <p>
      The <strong>Increments Inc. Design System</strong> is the single source of truth for our visual
      language. It defines the colors, typography, spacing, shadows, motion, voice, and components that
      every product screen, landing page, email, flyer, and deck must follow.
    </p>
    <p>
      It was distilled from real shipped work — the partner playbook, six partner-program flyers, and the
      Founding 25 campaign — and codified into a reusable set of tokens, components, and rules you can
      apply anywhere.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <Section title="Who this is for">
    <ul class="intro-audience">
      <li><strong>Designers</strong> — use the tokens and components in Figma; never invent a new color, radius, or shadow without a mapping here.</li>
      <li><strong>Engineers</strong> — import the CSS custom properties; reuse the Astro/React components; follow the usage rules.</li>
      <li><strong>Content &amp; marketing</strong> — follow the voice conventions, the italic-accent rule in headlines, and the non-negotiable contact footer format.</li>
      <li><strong>Founders &amp; leadership</strong> — approve new components against these principles; reject anything that breaks the system without cause.</li>
    </ul>
  </Section>

  <Section title="How the system is structured">
    <p>The system ships in three layers:</p>
    <ol class="intro-layers">
      <li>
        <strong>Brand Foundations</strong> — the 12 pages you're in now. Color, type, space, elevation,
        motion, logo, voice, accessibility, and tokens. Everything else inherits from here.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Components</strong> <span class="tag-soon">Coming</span> — buttons, inputs, tables, modals,
        navigation, data display. Built on the foundations.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Patterns</strong> <span class="tag-soon">Coming</span> — forms, dashboards, auth flows,
        onboarding, empty states. Composed from components.
      </li>
    </ol>
  </Section>

  <Section title="How to use this site">
    <ul class="intro-howto">
      <li><strong>Read foundations first.</strong> Skim all 12 pages before you design or build anything. They take less than an hour end-to-end.</li>
      <li><strong>Copy from the examples.</strong> Every page has live previews and copy-paste code. Don't reinvent.</li>
      <li><strong>Use tokens — never raw values.</strong> Never write <code>#C0FE71</code> in your stylesheet. Always <code>var(--color-brand-lime)</code>.</li>
      <li><strong>Respect the Do / Don't rules.</strong> Each was earned through a real shipping mistake — they're not stylistic preference.</li>
      <li><strong>Propose, don't invent.</strong> If a needed pattern isn't here, raise it — we'll add it properly so the next person doesn't re-invent.</li>
    </ul>
  </Section>

  <Callout variant="note" title="The north star">
    <p>
      <em>"Looks like a premium SaaS product brochure, not an agency flyer."</em>
    </p>
    <p>
      When in doubt, ask whether your work feels closer to a Stripe product page, a Linear release note,
      or an Increments flyer. If it doesn't, go back to the tokens and the components and rebuild from
      them.
    </p>
  </Callout>

  <Section title="Version & ownership">
    <p>
      <strong>Version:</strong> v0.1 · Brand Foundations shipped 2026-04-21.<br />
      <strong>Owner:</strong> <a href="mailto:ceo@incrementsinc.com">MSI Shamim, Founder &amp; CEO</a>.<br />
      <strong>Contributions:</strong> open a discussion before opening a PR — breaking foundation tokens
      ripples across every surface.
    </p>
  </Section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .intro-audience,
  .intro-layers,
  .intro-howto {
    padding-left: 0;
    list-style: none;
    max-width: 70ch;
  }

  .intro-audience li,
  .intro-howto li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 22px;
    margin-top: var(--space-5);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .intro-audience li::before,
  .intro-howto li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 10px;
    width: 10px;
    height: 10px;
    background: var(--color-brand-lime);
    border-radius: 2px;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-icon-tile);
  }

  .intro-layers {
    counter-reset: layer;
    list-style: none;
  }

  .intro-layers li {
    counter-increment: layer;
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 44px;
    margin-top: var(--space-7);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .intro-layers li::before {
    content: counter(layer, decimal-leading-zero);
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: -2px;
    font-family: var(--font-editorial);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: var(--type-weight-regular);
    font-size: 22px;
    color: var(--color-brand-lime);
  }

  .tag-soon {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 9.5px;
    font-weight: var(--type-weight-bold);
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-mute);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-soft);
    padding: 2px 7px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-pill);
    margin-left: 6px;
    vertical-align: 1px;
  }
</style>
